JUST LAUNCHED: On February 22nd  2011  a 6.3 magnitude earthquake ripped through the centre of Christchurch followed by severe aftershocks  destroying a city  a community  and the lives of thousands of people.  Levi’s® Skateboarding we were able to give back to a community in need  building a DIY Skate park in Christchurch for the city's youth. Levi’s® Skateboarding ambassadors Joey Pepper  Marius Syvanen  Al Partanen  Dan Plunkett  Josh Matthews and Pat Moran all flew from various parts of the United States to help with this project and to witness first hand the destruction 5 years on in Christchurch.  A huge thanks to the awesome team at Monster Children for capturing this build and the voices of the youth of Christchurch so well.  Check out the documentary now.

In 2008  BMW unveiled the BMW GINA Light Visionary Model: a concept car with a seamless  flexible  fabric outer shell stretched over a movable substructure  whose functions were only enabled when actually needed.   Today   BMW Group Designworks  and Puma are unveiling an innovative shoe inspired by the BMW GINA concept car: The X-CAT DISC.  Using only one thin layer of stretchable  super-light and lazer-cut GINA material  the shoe wraps around the foot like a second skin with no need for additional  uncomfortable seams.  Watch the video to see movement and material become one.

We need your help to find the last 25 percent of the affected top loaders and to ensure that Australians remain safe and well. As we reflect on National Reconciliation Week  we wanted to share the story of three IBMers who have embarked on the journey of a lifetime. Through our partnership with Jawun  Simon Webb  Ashlyn Mclean & Sandro Aiello have moved to an Indigenous community for the next six weeks.   Jawun  meaning 'friend' in the Kuku Yalanji language of Mossman Gorge  is a not-for-profit organisation that supports Indigenous people in achieving their own development goals.   These IBMers will be sharing their expertise  knowledge and skills around innovation and technology  rare outside of large towns and cities. By explaining its possibilities  they're hoping to affect real change in this community.  Pictured (from left): Ashlyn Mclean  Shane Webster  Jawun Regional Director  South Australia & Sandro Aiello. Reconciliation Australia #NRW #ThisisIBM

We’re cheering on the AFL’s Sir Douglas Nicholls Indigenous Round that kicked off in Sydney last night. In its honour  we wanted to share IBMer James Gallichan’s story.  James is a co-founder of the GO Foundation  along with Adam Goodes and Michael O'Loughlin  well-known Indigenous leaders and ex-Sydney Swans footballers. Their focus?  Providing educational opportunities to young Indigenous Australians so that they can achieve a brighter future.  We believe a diverse workplace makes coming to work a much richer experience. If you think you're hearing a lot about #blockchain  you'd be right. But what is it?  Essentially  blockchain is a special kind of database. What makes it so special is that it can store any kind of data. In the finance world  blockchains are ledgers (like spreadsheets)  but they accept inputs from lots of different parties. The ledger can't be changed unless all parties agree  making it more secure and it also means one central authority isn't approving all transactions.   Blockchain is disrupting Australian industries. Find out more about how we're empowering developers to design blockchain applications anywhere  via a highly secure and "tamper-resistant" cloud-based network: http://ow.ly/Mp6e30045Mt

Meet Jackson. He's a puppy learning to be a guide dog... but will he graduate?   Currently  as few as 37% of puppies make it through the raising program to become successful guide dogs. We've kicked-off a game-changing partnership with Sesame Workshop (the nonprofit educational organisation that produces Sesame Street) to advance early childhood education worldwide.  A generation ago  Sesame Street single-handedly transformed early childhood education  using television to teach children important basics like colours  numbers and letters of the alphabet. We're working together to develop the next generation of learning. How? By tapping into the power of cognitive computing from IBM Watson to enable personalised education where each child will essentially have their own "private tutor."   Find out more here: http://prn.to/1SQUPAM

What does an America’s Cup yacht  a Formula 1 race car and the fastest space taxi in the world have in common? All of them have been built with the help of Product Lifecycle Management (PLM) Software from Siemens: http://sie.ag/29fscwl #bringthecuphome
#Ducati on the use of our NX software: “Our engines  for example  are more powerful than ever before. That's important if we're to remain successful.” http://sie.ag/ducati
Manual work is becoming rare in manufacturing. Thanks to our software  motorbike manufacturer #Ducati were enabled to carry on their tradition and still lower time to market from 40 to 24 months
#Ducati on the use of our NX software: “Digitalization is making our motorbikes faster and more reliable. I'm proud of that.” http://sie.ag/ducati

#Ducati on the use of our NX software: “Digitalization helps us avoid errors. In the past  we used a classic torque wrench. Nowadays  an electric wrench saves details of every action – for our customers' safety.” http://sie.ag/ducati

Are you a motorbike fan? Us too! That’s why we are so excited about #Ducati using our software for their design and developing processes. Read an interview with Andrea Forni  Technical Director at Ducati: http://sie.ag/ducati

Today we celebrate a technical milestone: Our world-record electric motor made its first flight! Weighing a mere 50 kilograms  the motor has an output of 260 kilowatts  resulting in an unparalleled power-to-weight ratio. http://sie.ag/29qfv2t
Passion meets our software – nowhere else this combination works better than in Italy! Both are used by #Ducati to develop unique motorbikes that inspire people around the world. http://sie.ag/ducati

The new suspension bridge near Istanbul is especially earthquake-proof: About 390 sensors monitor its condition and raise the alarm in the event of excessive vibration. We delivered state-of-the-art traffic control technology for the 3km-long high-tech bridge over the Gulf of Izmit. http://sie.ag/29cIcyi

To mark the occasion of Werner von Siemens’ 200th birthday  we reconstructed his first workshop from 1847. As there are no surviving pictures of the interior  this had to be reconstructed based on written sources. Come and visit our new Munich headquarters  enjoy the replica of the historic workshop in the entrance area and gain fascinating insights into the production methods of the time.
At Siemens we care about dedication and the will to learn new things – not handicaps. Currently 6 000 people with disabilities contribute to Siemens’ success. http://sie.ag/28PBDk3
next47 will be able to unite the best of two worlds sie.ag/290lJSY

Starting on October 1  2016  next47 will foster disruptive ideas more vigorously and accelerate the development of new technologies. The new unit will be pooling our existing startup activities and have funding of €1 billion for the first five years. Find out more: sie.ag/290lJSY

Unconscious biases arise from our background  cultural environment and personal experiences. This may lead to poor decision making in a corporate environment. We think research should come out of the ivory tower and join forces with industry to make sure groundbreaking technologies can make their way to the market: http://sie.ag/28YlclV
How #unconsciousbias holds us back at work and how to prevent it. #InitiativeChefsache
